If you’re on the hunt for a gentle yet effective toner that delivers hydration and mild exfoliation, meet your new K-beauty must-have: Round Lab 1025 Dokdo Toner.

Infused with deep sea water from Ulleungdo Island, this toner is packed with 72 types of naturally derived minerals that soothe, hydrate, and balance the skin without irritation. Its watery, lightweight texture absorbs effortlessly, making it a perfect first step after cleansing. No heaviness, no stickiness—just pure hydration!

What makes it even better? It contains PHA (Gluconolactone), a gentle exfoliant that removes dead skin cells and unclogs pores while being safe for sensitive skin. Say goodbye to dullness and hello to smoother, more radiant skin with consistent use.

This toner is fragrance-free, alcohol-free, and cruelty-free, making it suitable for all skin types, especially if you’re looking for something calming and non-stripping. It preps your skin beautifully for the next steps in your skincare routine, helping your serums and moisturizers absorb even better.

I’ve been loving the glow it gives me—watch the reel to see the texture, application, and why it’s worth the hype!
